              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Scattering experiments were carried out with four",
                "natural silicon scatterers (92.2% 28Si, 4.7% 29Si",
                "and 3.1% 30Si) at 17 scaterring angles. The length",
                "of all scatterers was fixed at 20 cm, which was a",
                "compromise between high scattering yield and",
                "large flight-path differences. The scatternig plates",
                "consist of cylidrical silicon sticks placed close",
                "to each other with mean areas from 1.8 x 5.8 cm2 to",
                "3.6 x 11.6 cm2. The number of nuclei within the",
                "scatterer was 1.083, 1.803, 2.160, and 3.598x10**25,",
                "respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
